Package: interfacer
Title: Define and Enforce Interface Contracts for Dataframes
Version: 0.2.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Rob", "Challen", , "rob.challen@bristol.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5504-7768"))
Description: A dataframe validation framework for package builders who use dataframes
  as function parameters. It performs checks on column names, coerces
  datatypes, and checks grouping to make sure inputs conform to a specification. 
  It provides a mechanism for package authors to document expected 
  dataframe input formats and selectively dispatch to functions depending on the 
  format of a dataframe much like S3 does for classes. It also contains some
  developer tools to make working with and documenting dataframe specifications
  easier.
